You see the source of the chanting: a group of cultists in black robes encircle an alter.\n\nOne of the cultists opens his eyes and looks straight at you.\n\nSomeone hits you on the head from behind. The world fades to darkness.\n\nWhen you awaken, you are tied to the alter. The cultists are still chanting, surrounding you. Just beside your head, a cultist looks at you and smiles. His teeth are sharpened to points.\n\n//Oh, hell no.// You strain with all of your strength against the bindings. The cultists have all opened their eyes now. They are all smiling and walking towards you. Suddenly, the ropes snap because of your extreme skill at violence.\n\nSoon all of the cultists are dead. A huge fist cracks against your ear and you collapse to the floor.\n\nThe philosopher towers over your prone form and shakes his head. "It is better to be violent, if there is violence in our hearts, than to put on the cloak of nonviolence to cover incompetence."\n\nOne of the other philosophers retorts in outrage: "Nonviolence is a powerful and just weapon which cuts without wounding and ennobles the man who weilds it!"\n\nGroaning, you crawl away while they are distracted by their debate.\n\n[[Onwards.|trainhub]]

He comes leaping over the tops of the file cabinets, gibbering madly. "Please, tell me all the details!" he cries. "I must know! For I am... EUSTACE O'CONNELL, OFFICIAL TRAIN GOVERNMENT CENSUS-TAKER AND RECORDS-KEEPER!!"\n\n"Oh," you say. "Thanks. I was wondering."\n\nHe huddles on top of the nearest filing cabinet, paper and pencil-stib in hand. "So what is it?" he asks. "A birth? A death?
